# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Panoptica365 .gitignore
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Anything matching these patterns will NEVER be tracked by git.
# This is the single most important file in the repo for safety:
# if a secret is accidentally committed, removing it from history
# requires git-filter-repo + force-push. Get this right on commit #1.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── SECRETS — never commit, no exceptions ───
.env
.env.local
.env.production
.env.development
.env.*.local
# Backups produced by `sed -i.bak ...` and friends. Added May 20, 2026
# after a `.env.bak` (containing live secrets) was almost committed
# during the legacy-schema cleanup. Belt-and-suspenders catches any
# .bak file generated by ad-hoc shell commands editing config files.
.env.bak
.env.bak.*
*.bak
# Keep .env.template / .env.example committed as placeholders for newcomers:
!.env.template
!.env.example

# ─── Cryptographic material ───
*.pem
*.key
*.pfx
*.p12
*.crt
*.cer
*.thumbprint

# ─── Operational data — host-specific, never ships in source ───
data/
backups/
logs/
snapshots/
certs/
reports/
uploads/
exports/

# ─── Personal scratchpads / customer-identifying notes ───
Links to consoles.txt

# ─── Personal/internal working files (not part of the shipped app) ───
claude api usage/
dev/Panoptica/
Documentation/
# Internal-only root-level docs — guidance/notes for Claude sessions and ops,
# not shipped to MSPs. (README.md stays tracked — it IS public-facing.)
RELEASING.md
DR-RESTORE.md
i18n-snapshot-log.md

# ─── Node.js ───
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.npm
.node_repl_history
*.tgz
.pnp.*

# ─── SMB / macOS / Linux / editor artifacts ───
.DS_Store
._*
.smbdelete*
.fuse_hidden*
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.tmp
*.tmp.*

# ─── Test/debug scratchpads from past iterations ───
.bash-write-test
.invalidate_cache
.probe.txt
.test-touch
probe-*.txt
scripts/_test_report_input.json

# ─── LCARS theme leftovers (retired Apr 2026, snapshots only) ───
public/css/panoptica-LCARS-original.css
public/css/panoptica.css.lcars-backup
public/css/themes/lcars.css.archive

# ─── Python bytecode + venv (auto-generated) ───
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
# ReportLab venv — provisioned by panoptica-setup.sh / Dockerfile, never committed.
venv/

# ─── IDEs ───
.vscode/
.idea/
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace

# ─── Build / cache ───
dist/
build/
.cache/
.parcel-cache/
.tmp/

# ─── Per-user tooling (Claude environment, etc.) ───
.claude/

# ─── Runtime logs ───
*.log

# ─── Database dumps ───
*.sql.gz
*.tar.gz
*.dump
mysqldump-*.sql

# ─── OS metadata ───
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# License server public key (safe to commit — public half of Ed25519 pair)
!keys/license-server-public-key.pem

# Updater-managed image pin (written at runtime by panoptica-updater; never commit)
docker-compose.override.yml

# Payload signing PRIVATE key — Ed25519 release key. NEVER commit (already
# covered by *.key above; named explicitly so nobody adds an exception for it).
# The PUBLIC half scripts/sidecar/panoptica-release.pub IS committed.
panoptica-release.key
